    "Let V = {v ∈ S | v ⊥ y ′ }, so V ∈ RO(S, ⊑) by the same reasoning as above.",
    "Since y ′ ⊑ y, y ̸ ∈ V, which with xR i y implies x ̸ ∈ ■ i V. But it also follows from our supposition that ∀x′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′: x ′′ ∈ ■ i V. Thus, ■ i V does not satisfy refinability, so ■ i V ̸ ∈ RO(S, ⊑).",
    "But then since V ∈ RO(S, ⊑), RO(S, ⊑) is not closed under ■ i.As an immediate corollary of Proposition 2.30, we have the following (recall Definitions 2.21 and 2.25).Corollary 2.31 (Interplay of R i and ⊑ for Full Possibility Frames).1.",
